In [4]:
#scaling data to pixel size 

Clust['Cell V']=(Clust['Pixel size microns']**3)*(Clust['Cell Volume'])
Clust['Nuc V']=(Clust['Pixel size microns']**3)*(Clust['Nucleus Volume'])
Clust['Cell A']=(Clust['Pixel size microns']**2)*(Clust['Cell Area '])
Clust['Nuc A']=(Clust['Pixel size microns']**2)*(Clust['Nucleus Area '])
Clust['Mito V']=(Clust['Pixel size microns']**3)*(Clust['Mitochondria Volume'])
Clust['Mito A']=(Clust['Pixel size microns']**2)*(Clust['Mitochondria Area'])
Clust['Endo V']=(Clust['Pixel size ']**3)*(Clust['Endosome Volume'])
Clust['Endo A']=(Clust['Pixel size microns']**2)*(Clust['Endosome Area'])
Clust['Ld V']=(Clust['Pixel size ']**3)*(Clust['Lipid Volume'])
Clust['Ld A']=(Clust['Pixel size microns']**3)*(Clust['Lipid Area'])
In [5]:
# calculating mathematical parameters

#nucleus
Clust['Rel Nuc V']=Clust['Nucleus Volume']/Clust['Cell Volume']
Clust['Rel Nuc A']=Clust['Nucleus Area ']/Clust['Cell Area ']
Clust['Cell A/V']=Clust['Cell Area ']/Clust['Cell Volume']
Clust['Nuc A/V']=Clust['Nucleus Area ']/Clust['Nucleus Volume']

#mitochondria
Clust['Rel Mito V']=Clust['Mitochondria Volume']/Clust['Cell Volume']
Clust['Rel Mito A']=Clust['Mitochondria Area']/Clust['Cell Area ']
Clust['Mito A/V']=Clust['Mitochondria Area']/Clust['Mitochondria Volume']

#endosomes
Clust['Rel Endo V']=Clust['Endosome Volume']/Clust['Cell Volume']
Clust['Rel Endo A']=Clust['Endosome Area']/Clust['Cell Area ']
Clust['Endo A/V']=Clust['Endosome Area']/Clust['Endosome Volume']

#lipids
Clust['Rel Ld V']=Clust['Lipid Volume']/Clust['Cell Volume']
Clust['Rel Ld A']=Clust['Lipid Area']/Clust['Cell Area ']
Clust['Ld A/V']=Clust['Lipid Area']/Clust['Lipid Volume']

#plotting lipid volume

plt.figure(figsize=(5,5), dpi=600)
sns.set(font='sans serif')
sns.set(style="whitegrid")

order=["M1_6h", "M1_24h",  "M2_6h", "M2_24h"]
ax=sns.boxplot(data=Clust_lipids, x=Clust_lipids['State'], y=Clust_lipids['Ld V'], hue=Clust_lipids['State'],palette=my_colors)

comparisons = [("M1_6h", "M1_24h"), ("M2_6h", "M2_24h")]

annotator = Annotator(ax, comparisons, data=Clust_lipids, x="State", y=Clust_lipids['Ld V'])
annotator.configure(test='t-test_ind', text_format='star', loc='inside', verbose=2)
annotator.apply_and_annotate()

ax = plt.gca()
new_labels = ['M1 6h', 'M1 24h', 'M2a 6h', 'M2a 24h']
ax.set_xticklabels(new_labels)  
ax.tick_params(axis='x', labelsize=12)
ax.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=12)
ax.set_ylabel('Lipid droplet Volume,$nm^3$', fontsize=14)
ax.set_xlabel('Microglia State', fontsize=14)
ax.set_ylim(0, 1.5e+08)
plt.legend().remove()
plt.savefig('F:\\Microglia project\\Soft X-ray tomography\\2023\Analysis\\Graphs\\Lipid_Volume_per_conditions.png',dpi=600, bbox_inches='tight')

#creating barplot based on how many cells have or have not lipid droplets

cell_counts = Clust.groupby('State').size()
positive_counts = Clust[Clust['Lipid Volume'] > 0].groupby('State').size()
negative_counts = Clust[Clust['Lipid Volume'] == 0].groupby('State').size()

positive_ratio=(positive_counts/cell_counts)*100
negative_ratio=(negative_counts/cell_counts)*100

print(positive_ratio)
print(negative_ratio)
